					%h2
						HTML
					%p
						HTML stands for Hyper Text Markup Language and is the primary building block of the web. It is used by browsers to render text, display images, create forms, etc. Any intro to web design, web programming, and so forth is going to teach you HTML. 
				.span4
					%h2
						CSS
					%p
						CSS stands for Cascading Style Sheets. CSS controls the general formatting of a web site. In other words, how far apart buttons are, the font of some text, the weight of said font, which graphics to use for what types of buttons, the color of the background, and so on. It is used to style HTML, basically.
				.span4
					%h2
						JavaScript
					%p
						JavaScript is one of the main programming languages of the web. You simply CAN NOT be a front-end web developer without knowing JavaScript. It is responsible for a lot of the 'cool' animations that websites can do. If you see something fade, pop, move, or shidizzle on the web page, then JavaScript is probably the language that made it happen. JavaScript alters the behavior of web pages. 
