					%h2
						HAML
					%p
						HAML is HTML simplified. It just makes HTML prettier and easier to work with. Because of a lot of web technologies are kind of long in the tooth, there have been recent movements to stream line them and make them more modern. CoffeeScript, for example, is similar to HAML since it replaces the core functionality that JavaScript provides with something simpler to read and write.
				.span4
					%br
					%h2
						Ruby
					%p
						Ruby is the awesome programming language that I will be teaching the class with. Similar to Python, it is an object-oriented, high-level language. Ruby was the language used to build the extremely popular web framework 'Ruby on Rails'. It is incredibly powerful and easy to read.
				.span4
					%br
					%h2
						Sinatra
					%p
						Sinatra is a web framework that is a viable alternative to Ruby on Rails. I've found that it is a lot simpler than Rails and easier to work with. I will avoid the internals of Sinatra. and instead briefly go over what a web server is.
